Description: Small conical cup or lid of Nile silt pottery with flaring sides tapering to a rounded point. Pinched at rim; surfaces smoothed but untreated.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Hiw, R164 (Register) R134 (scratched on vessel)
Curator's comments: R134 marked on side of vessel. Grave discussed in W.M.F Petrie and A.C. Mace, Diospolis Parva, London (1901), p. 35.
